snippet: Shadowed by the violence in neighboring Ukraine, the vote became another fierce contest between the West and Russia for influence in a former Soviet republic.
abstract: Preliminary results from Moldova's parliamentary elections show three pro-European political parties will control country's Parliament, even though pro-Russian Socialist Party made surprising first-place finish.
lead_paragraph: Shadowed by the violence in neighboring Ukraine, the vote became another fierce contest between the West and Russia for influence in a former Soviet republic.

headline.main: Moldova Vote Gives Edge to Parties Looking West
headline.print_headline: Moldova Vote Gives Edge to Parties Looking West
